The paper discusses the use of normalization methods in overparametrized models like neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the weight normalization method and its variant, which are optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the convergence rate of the methods, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the methods in least squares regression and matrix sensing, which are topics in data science and computer vision, respectively, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) possible sub-categories.
